<section class="mb-5">
    <h1 class="mb-3">Hi, I'm Hexagon</h1>
    <p class="lead-text">I've been immersed in JavaScript since 1995, creating libraries like <strong>Croner</strong> and <strong>@hexagon/base64</strong>. My blog covers everything from JavaScript and TypeScript to modern runtimes like Deno.</p>
    <p>For a solid foundation in JavaScript, start with my <a href="/posts/guide-to-js/introduction/">JavaScript Guide</a>. </p>
    <p>This blog is built using <a href="https://deno.land" target="_blank">Deno</a> and <a href="https://lume.land" target="_blank">Lume</a>, and the source code is available at <a href="https://github.com/hexagon/blog">github.com/hexagon/blog</a>.</p>
    <h2 class="mb-4 mt-5">Recent posts</h2>
    <ul class="list-unstyled">
    {% for post in search.pages("","date=desc") %}
        {% if loop.index0 < 20 and post.data.title != "Home" %}    
            <li>
                <article>
                    <time class="text-muted small" datetime="{{ post.data.date }}">{{ post.data.date | date }}</time>
                    <h3 class="mt-1"><a href="{{ post.data.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a></h3>
                </article>
            </li>
        {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
    </ul>
</section>